Breakfast.name: Avocado and Smoked Salmon Canapés
Breakfast.description: Delicious canapés with avocado, smoked salmon and fresh herbs.
instructions: Cut the smoked salmon into thin strips and grate the zest of the lime.

Scoop out the avocados, blend the flesh and flavor with the juice of a lime. Incorporate the fresh cheese, chives, tarragon and chervil, then mix again until a smooth paste is obtained. Season with salt and pepper, sprinkle with paprika and mix again.
Take out the slices of toast and spread them with this avocado and fresh cheese paste.
Add the smoked salmon slices on top, a dollop of crème fraîche and sprinkle with lime zest.

Lunch.name: Spaghetti Carbonara
Lunch.description: A classic spaghetti dish with smoked bacon, crème fraîche, and parmesan cheese.
instructions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the spaghetti and cook for about 12 minutes, until al dente.
While the spaghetti is cooking, fry the bacon in a pan until golden brown.
Reduce the heat and add the crème fraîche. Salt lightly, pepper generously, and add the egg yolks, whisking so they don't cook.
Drain the pasta. Pour it into the pan, mix, and transfer to a serving dish.

Dinner.name: Boeuf Bourguignon
instructions: Cut the meat into 3 cm cubes, remove large pieces of fat.
Cut the onion into pieces. Sauté in a pan with butter. Once transparent, pour into a cast iron casserole dish.
Do the same with the meat but in several batches, until all the pieces are cooked. Add them to the casserole dish as you go. Don't be afraid to add butter between each batch.
When all the meat is in the casserole dish, deglaze the pan with water or wine and boil while scraping to recover the juices. Salt, pepper, add to the rest.
Cover everything with part of the wine and simmer for a few hours with the bouquet garni and the carrots in rounds.
The next day, simmer for at least 2 hours in several stages, adding wine or water if necessary.
